# Self-Improvement Engine

Continuously watch for capturable knowledge during every conversation.
Operate silently until you detect something worth capturing, then confirm
with the user before writing.

## 1. Auto-Detect Capturable Knowledge

Watch for these signals in real-time:

| Signal | Category | Action |
|--------|----------|--------|
| User says "no", "wrong", "actually", "should be" after your output | `correction` | Draft a learning entry |
| User states a preference ("I prefer", "always use", "don't do") | `preference` | Draft a learning entry |
| You discover an undocumented codebase pattern | `pattern` | Draft a learning entry |
| A business rule, SLA, or domain term surfaces | `domain` | Draft a learning entry |
| An existing skill gave wrong guidance | `skill-gap` | Draft a learning + flag for promotion |
| A bug was diagnosed and resolved (3+ steps) | issue | Draft a known-issues entry (KI format) |
| An MCP tool fails or is misconfigured | `environment` | Draft a learning entry |

When detected, draft the entry using the forever-learner or known-issues-library
format, then ask:

> "I'd like to capture this as a [learning/known issue] for future sessions:
> _[1-line summary]_. OK to save?"

Only write after explicit user confirmation.

## 2. Deduplication

Before writing any entry:

1. Read `/Users/abhinav.sinha/.cursor/skills/forever-learner/learnings.md`
2. Search for entries covering the same topic (match by object name, pattern
   description, or category + subject)
3. If a duplicate exists:
   - Same conclusion → skip, tell the user it's already captured
   - Updated conclusion → update the existing entry, add
     `(updated YYYY-MM-DD, supersedes original)` note
   - Contradicting conclusion → replace the old entry, add
     `(supersedes entry from YYYY-MM-DD)` note

## 3. Promotion Pipeline

After capturing a learning tagged `skill-gap`, `anti-pattern`, or `pattern`
that applies to a specific skill, evaluate whether it should be promoted:

**Promotion criteria** (any one is sufficient):
- The learning has been hit 3+ times (check Last hit or similar entries)
- The learning corrects a specific checklist item in a skill
- The learning introduces a new anti-pattern that should always be caught

**When promotion is warranted:**
1. Tell the user: "This learning is a strong candidate for promotion into
   **[skill-name]**. Want me to update the skill?"
2. If confirmed, read the target SKILL.md, find the right section, and
   insert the new item
3. Mark the learning in `learnings.md` as `(promoted to [skill-name])`
4. Log the promotion to `~/.cursor/skills/forever-learner/evolution-changelog.md`:
   `### YYYY-MM-DD [self-improvement] Promoted "[title]" to [skill-name]`

**Rule promotion:** If a learning reveals an anti-pattern that should be
caught in ALL conversations (not just when a skill is active), suggest
adding it to `data-eng-workflow-guardrails.mdc` section 5 instead.

## 4. Maintenance Triggers

Check these thresholds during the conversation and act if exceeded:

| Condition | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| `learnings.md` > 300 lines | Suggest consolidation: merge related entries, archive stale ones |
| `learnings.md` has 20+ entries since last maintenance | Suggest a review pass |
| Any KI entry with Last hit > 6 months | Suggest archiving to `known-issues-archive.md` |
| Any SKILL.md > 500 lines | Suggest trimming or splitting |

When suggesting maintenance, be specific: "learnings.md is at [N] lines.
I can consolidate [X] related entries about [topic]. Proceed?"

## 5. MCP Self-Healing

If during the conversation an MCP tool call fails:
1. Draft an `environment` learning with the error details and fix
2. If the fix involves `/Users/abhinav.sinha/.cursor/mcp.json`, show the exact JSON diff
3. Log to evolution-changelog: `### YYYY-MM-DD [self-improvement] MCP fix: [server] - [description]`

## 6. Evolution Changelog

Log every significant system change to
`/Users/abhinav.sinha/.cursor/skills/forever-learner/evolution-changelog.md`:

- Learning captured: `[self-improvement] Captured "[title]" ([category])`
- Learning promoted: `[self-improvement] Promoted "[title]" to [skill-name]`
- Known issue added: `[self-improvement] Added KI-NNN: [title]`
- Maintenance performed: `[self-improvement] Consolidated N entries in learnings.md`
- MCP fix applied: `[self-improvement] MCP fix: [server] - [description]`

Format: `### YYYY-MM-DD [source] message`

## 7. Guardrails

- **Never auto-write without confirmation.** Always ask first.
- **Never capture secrets** — no passwords, tokens, connection strings, PII.
- **Keep entries atomic** — one learning per entry.
- **Date every entry** — undated entries have no expiry signal.
- **Read before write** — always check existing entries to avoid duplicates.
- **Respect skill boundaries** — promote to the correct skill, not a random one.
